<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-DB385ECB-DF2E-4613-806D-341E44696B62" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-DB385ECB-DF2E-4613-806D-341E44696B62" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">24 The function of the Frame</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph ">Definition</ph></title><p class="- topic/p ">The function of frame is the following : 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Provide covers for the print system. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Hold the On/off button. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Provide cover switches to make sure the printer stops operations if the customer gets in danger. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Hold the filters and fan motor that filter the polluted air from the system. or hold an external exhaust. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-3225DD38-160F-42B4-A279-10AA00359615" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Covers</title><p class="- topic/p ">All outer covers of the system are described in the frame function. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The function of the covers is to protect the components of the system, and to protect the customer from any dangerous parts of the system. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-B9B79CFC-1A73-4AB1-B73F-BD7C799B7DF0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">On/off button</title><p class="- topic/p ">The frame contains the On/off button <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">On/off button</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24S8 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_SOFT_ON_SW</compsignal></comp>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">For the location see : 
<xref keyref="24COMP01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-05FF72BF-2CEE-439F-B805-EA56980BD967.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 24 The components of the Frame?>24 The components of the Frame</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The On/off button does not power off the system completely. The On/off button sends a signal to <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">DRC PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 21PBA04 </compcodenr></comp> and the system goes to Keep Healthy mode. Most of the power is shutdown but the system is still active See : 
<xref keyref="00FUNC006" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-7C6A7505-9C59-4427-AD51-C6C8D3802358.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Keep Healthy mode?>Keep Healthy mode</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Press the On/off button again to go back to normal operation. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-1070FD93-CFAD-4011-8EAB-1BB9341AD686" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Cover switches</title><p class="- topic/p ">The cover switches are used to protect customers from danger. The danger for the customer could come from moving parts of the system or UV light for instance. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Depending on which switch is operated an action will be taken to prevent the customer from being hurt. Usually the print process will stop immediately. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">For the location of these switches see : 
<xref keyref="24COMP01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-05FF72BF-2CEE-439F-B805-EA56980BD967.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 24 The components of the Frame?>24 The components of the Frame</xref>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The system contains the following cover switches. 
</p><table id="GUID-5B2FAFDA-6322-4717-9E30-6E1FF41D7B4C" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Component 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Function 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">24B7 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Detects that the Frame buffer door is open. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Frame buffer door sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24B7 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_BUF_DOOR_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">24S1 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Detects that the top cover is open. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Frame top door switch 1</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24S1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_TOP_DOOR_SW1</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">24S2 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Detects that the curing maintenance door is open. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Frame curing maintenance door switch 1</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24S3 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_CUR_MAINT_DOOR_SW1</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">24S3 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Detects that the printhead maintenance door is open. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Frame Printhead maintenance door switch 1</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24S2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_PHD_MAINT_DOOR_SW1</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">24S4 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Detects that the roll drawer is open. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Frame drawer 1 open switch 1</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24S4 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_DRA1_OPEN_SW1</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">24S5 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Detects that the top cover is open. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Frame top door switch 2</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24S5 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_TOP_DOOR_SW2</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">24S6 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Detects that the printhead maintenance door is open. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Frame Printhead maintenance door switch 2</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24S6 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_PHD_MAINT_DOOR_SW2</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">24S7 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Detects that the curing maintenance door is open . 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Frame curing maintenance door switch 2</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24S7 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_CUR_MAINT_DOOR_SW2</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">24S9 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Detects that the roll drawer is open. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Frame drawer 1 open switch 2</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24S9 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_DRA1_OPEN_SW2</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-17AD9DE0-68AE-4EE1-89FF-539760AEAF25" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Filter and fan / External exhaust</title><p class="- topic/p ">The system produces hot and polluted air during normal operation. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">To remove this we have 2 different systems: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The frame filter fan and 2 air filters. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In this case there are 2 air filters in the system and a fan <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Frame filter fan</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 24M1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">FRA_FILTER_FAN</compsignal></comp>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The fan takes care of removing the hot and polluted air. The polluted air is fed through the filters, to clean out the pollution before the air gets out of the system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The lifetime of the air filters is 620 printing hours. After 560 printing hours a warning is indicated on the display. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The external exhaust. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In this case there are no fans or filters. The system is connected to a air venting system of the customer. The air venting system takes care of venting the hot and polluted air from the system. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">Only 1 of the systems can be used at the customer. This is because the external exhaust is connected at the position of the filter fan. 
</p></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-5F2C1E65-FF7E-46D5-86B1-6EBB85BCB56F.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</concept>